verbose_text: The protein levels of GFP- TDegF Cdc28 in YSM005 (P_CDC19 -600 -GFP - TDegF CDC28) were highly reduced in the presence of the TEV plasmid compared with the vector control, and the level was lower under the -Ura-Leu condition, where the expression of pTEV + increased, than the -Ura condition.
